[2026-03-09T00:43:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XmsoFPf1VhjJETg2su8ZXX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found the code related to the project info page in this codebase. Here are the key components:\n\n### 1. **UI/TUI - Project Detail Page** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`)\n\nThis is the main template that displays:\n- **Project Info Panel** (lines 25-29): Shows docker image, version, and prompt files section\n- **Orchestrator Control Panel** (lines 11-23): Controls for enabling/disabling workflow orchestration\n- **Workflows Panel** (lines 31-38): Displays workflow DAGs\n- **Step Drawer** (lines 40-47): Slides in from the right to show step details\n\n### 2. **Expandable Prompts Section with HTML `<details>` Element** (lines 98-117)\n\n```\n<details><summary class=\"mono\">Prompt Files</summary>\n  <!-- History entries with click handlers -->\n</details>\n```\n\nThe \"Prompts section\" uses native HTML `<details>` and `<summary>` elements for expandable functionality with built-in browser arrows.\n\n### 3. **Backend API Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n- **`handleAPIProjectInfo()`** (lines 939-1025): Fetches project metadata\n  - Reads Docker image from Dockerfile (lines 945-959)\n  - Reads version from `.cloche/version` file (lines 961-968)\n  - **Fetches git commit history** using `git log` (line 989):\n    ```go\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n    ```\n    Returns: commit SHA, date, and message for each prompt file\n\n- **`handleAPIPromptDiff()`** (lines 1027-1056): Fetches file diffs between commits\n  - Uses `git diff` command (line 1047): \n    ```go\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n    ```\n  - Returns diff output as plain text\n\n- **`handleAPIStepContent()`** (lines 1134-1199): Fetches step content from files or inline config\n  - Reads prompt files (line 1178)\n  - Reads script files (lines 1189-1196)\n  - Returns file contents as plain text\n\n### 4. **Frontend JavaScript Logic** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` lines 89-139)\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n- **`loadProjectInfo()`** (lines 89-121): Calls API to load project info and renders HTML with:\n  - Docker image and version metadata\n  - Prompt files with commit history in expandable sections\n  \n- **`toggleDiff()`** (lines 123-139): Handles clicking on commit entries\n  - Fetches the git diff from the API\n  - Inserts a `<pre class=\"diff-block\">` element below the clicked entry\n  - Can toggle the diff on/off by clicking again\n\n### 5. **Styling** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` lines 197-221)\n\n```css\ndetails {\n    margin: 0.5rem 0;\n}\n\ndetails summary {\n    cursor: pointer;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    color: var(--text-muted);\n}\n\ndetails pre {\n    background: var(--bg-surface);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: var(--radius);\n    padding: 0.75rem;\n    /* ... overflow and text styling ... */\n}\n```\n\nAlso styles the diff block:\n```css\n.diff-block {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    /* ... styling for diffs ... */\n}\n```\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n- **Web Handler (API endpoints)**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- **Project Detail Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- **Styling**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n- **Layout Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a75c77e064e43aa08 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51023\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 27974</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b45cf3d1-b3cb-4cc4-9a8b-9d828c396ebb","uuid":"dd5a6815-5c63-4543-ac7f-e6a9a458bcbb","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code related to the \"project info page\" in this codebase. Specifically, I'm looking for:\n1. The UI/TUI code that displays project information\n2. Any \"Prompts section\" that has expansion arrows\n3. Code that fetches or displays file contents vs git commits\n\nSearch thoroughly - look in cmd/, internal/, and any UI-related directories. Search for keywords like \"prompt\", \"expand\", \"project info\", \"commits\", \"file contents\", \"section\".","agentId":"a75c77e064e43aa08","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found the code related to the project info page in this codebase. Here are the key components:\n\n### 1. **UI/TUI - Project Detail Page** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`)\n\nThis is the main template that displays:\n- **Project Info Panel** (lines 25-29): Shows docker image, version, and prompt files section\n- **Orchestrator Control Panel** (lines 11-23): Controls for enabling/disabling workflow orchestration\n- **Workflows Panel** (lines 31-38): Displays workflow DAGs\n- **Step Drawer** (lines 40-47): Slides in from the right to show step details\n\n### 2. **Expandable Prompts Section with HTML `<details>` Element** (lines 98-117)\n\n```\n<details><summary class=\"mono\">Prompt Files</summary>\n  <!-- History entries with click handlers -->\n</details>\n```\n\nThe \"Prompts section\" uses native HTML `<details>` and `<summary>` elements for expandable functionality with built-in browser arrows.\n\n### 3. **Backend API Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n- **`handleAPIProjectInfo()`** (lines 939-1025): Fetches project metadata\n  - Reads Docker image fro